@PatriotAmbassador820 @Joker1 Just a speculative thought, but earning delay was possibly related to providing complete data to the court, along with share ownerships details from ShareIntel and Buyinsdotnet.  Wes could be looking to make a slam dunk case to the judge for court ruling. 

It is very easy to dismiss that RH is not able to come up with an ER, some folks forget that these are special circumstances - lawyers, auditors, Wes, ShareIntel, Buyinsdotnet, Upstream, MERJ, M&A (Jefferies)... all are engaged here. 

I don't claim to know what the reality is, NOBODY can... but it seems too obvious that they cannot produce ER due to financial numbers not ticking and tying.  There is more to it. IMHO $GNS Bullish

@Joker1 I hear ya, and what I am thinking is either the court order damages (lump sum) will include all settlement of synthetic/NSS/counterfeit et al. one amount with warning to not NSS GNS going forward, based on data points shared by Wes/lawyers - WallSt loves settlements.  (we have precedence) 

OR, 

The court orders brokerages to provide share ownership before ordering damages, and that triggers a full-blown short squeeze.  (we have precedence) ($GNS Bullish

@785kx7 @soldierofcourage I believe buyback is already authorized and the $GNS BOD can commence anytime. 

"The Company Board has approval to execute a share repurchase mandate at such time that they may choose within the next 12 months." 
globenewswire.com/news-rele... Bullish

@plumsmooth because they need shares to cover!  At these prices nobody is selling (large blocks), and float maybe just locked up. 

On the other hand, point about most market players are short and not covering could be true.  Given macro conditions and Fed hawkish communication there really is no reason for anyone to cover - algos set to naked short any buying pressure.   

Except few scenarios like $GNS, where there could be material action about to unfold.  M&A Bullish

@lottomillions @greekiserectus Ah but how do you know shorters are covering or even able to cover, if there are 400M naked shares sold short?  The CEO has confirmed fraud and has engaged legal, NSS layers, buyin.net/, shareintel, RICO lawyers... and you have definitive proof that all of them are engaged here are useless? 

I don't see the nonsense until the court ruling, until then, the nonsense here is the people who spread FUD. 

If I ever felt that an investment had gone south, I would leave and not continue to post FUD on boards, that is for emotional traders, trolls... GL $GNS Bullish

@JJI356 @chucky1110 Sure if you have a relatively small share count.  I would like to engage in the Upstream process, since GNS is one of the few tickers that are going to be dual listed as part of Blockchain. 

I am hearing one of the twitter spaces right now and one of the CEOs (not RH) was mentioning about blockchain and education using AI will be things to look forward to.   

I am convinced that out of this banking mess, blockchain will likely emerge as the next technology that markets will gravitate towards, as GNS and others set the successful precedence, that of - riddance from illegal shorting, counterfeits, IOUs, NSS, et al. a new market, after which CEOs can actually focus on building their business and positively impacting longterm shareholders.  $GNS Bullish

@Prince314 @Nothing_Guy what they can do and I suspect they are is, shake buy shake buy to grab as many cheap shares, then as it goes up, use retail sells to cover while remaining long on the cheaper buys.

But some short HF is stuck here large (ones that piggybacked on alto game plan) and unable to do anything, until a forced covering is issued by legal / court.  Covering is going to be expensive so they are not going to willingly handover millions.
$GNS Bullish

@Prince314 Nope, can only burn IOUs, that to, if sellers are more than buyers.  At this level doubtful with all the catalysts we are aware of, thanks to a one of a kind CEO.

In order to cover they need real shares, good luck covering without a squeeze.  IMHO
$GNS Bullish

@greekiserectus @Booger4116 GNS will expose it for sure, all lies in the data gathered by Shareintel/Buyins/Wes/lawyers/CEO/Board.   

But, not just that, it's mindboggling how strategically coordinated and colluded this manipulation exists in the markets.  The entire Fk'in system is "engaged" and has the system engineered by design by the upper echelons to syphon money from retail.  I would really like to see education courses designed to expose this so the next generation does not go through what I/we have gone through unknowingly in these markets. 

$GNS Bullish

@plumsmooth HFs probably thinking the same, backdoor into blockchain - doubt it.  HFs can't pay for it, so legit brokerages will force and short covering and collect it from the rogue broker.  Time to pay for sins.  In GME, AMC they could afford to pay as cost of doing business (couple of billions meh), in this case open market forced covering to burndown the IOUs. 

Roger has got all he who's who of NSS engaged here, including powerful legal representation, NSS trackers (shareintel, buyins) and mentors (Patrick B), and, I am sure more are there in the background. 

No need to worry, they are thinking 10 steps ahead (recall - playing chess vs checkers)  $GNS Bullish

@Joker1 A variant of the same question I have is - Why don't I know whether I own REAL co issued shares or not? after T+x settlement! WTF, efficient markets my a$$.  SEC does not do anything but simply manage the colossal fraud going on in markets. 

The digital nature of the trading system has clouded the basic share ownership and that has given some entities to come up with engineered solutions for fraudulent activity and illicit profits. 

I really liked Roger words on - value creators vs value destroyers. Bullish

@Cheggers it takes a certain aptitude to understand and connect the dots in this century’s biggest disruptive technology… think Internet in last century.

IMHO.  Probably a lot of traders, trolls and few investors here, so the narratives are wide ranging.

As a LT investor it’s about profitability in 2024-2025, and along the way see margin improvement as Green H2 production and distribution to $PLUG customers ramp up.  And any adjacent mkt expansion is cherry on top! Bullish

@calv @AshHydrogen Also, the subtle comment that many may have missed in the PLUG ER, $PLUG has been working with $MSFT for 2.5 yrs on fuel cells for data centers and now they have announced the solution readiness.  MSFT Exec had mentioned that any solution will have to be more cost effective than current diesel-based solution. That speaks volumes, IMHO, to the fact that customers look at cost as the forefront driver in making long-term investment decisions, especially in regard to disruptive technology for running core business operations.   

MSFT waited until PTC/IRA Bill was almost a done deal and PLUG was churning out Green H2 from Plants already build out, with a goal of 70tpd 2022 (NA), 500tpd 2025 (NA), 1000tpd 2028 (latter includes Europe), and only then are ready to probably ink a larger deal (JV with equity stake) to jointly expand adjacent markets for Green h2 and fuel cells. 

IMHO Bullish

@Chuckwgn Biden is only talking "emergency" now because US has failed to take a leadership role and is being dragged by the rest of the world to join in or become a developing country in the decades to come.  The energy transition is aggressively being undertaken by the rest of the world. 

How dumb can US Gov be when they have $PLUG in their backyard, and instead of driving policies to take leadership role, all they do is blowing smoke past us to the coming generations (pun intended). 

Having said that, finally seeing Andy being called in for senator level discussions is encouraging but time will tell. Bullish
